-- Zydus Wellness Surges in Mumbai Trading on Speculation Net Profit May Rise
-- Adi Narayan
-- 2010-07-16T09:08:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/zydus-wellness-surges-in-mumbai-trading-on-speculation-net-profit-may-rise.html

          
          
             Zydus Wellness Ltd. , India’s largest
producer of sugar-free sweeteners by market share, surged to the
highest in more than 14 years in Mumbai trading on speculation
the company may report higher earnings.  
 Zydus rose 5.4 percent to 558 rupees as of 2:11 p.m., the
 highest  since January 1996, based on earliest data available on
the Bloomberg. India’s benchmark Sensitive Index gained 0.2
percent.  
 The Ahmedabad-based company is scheduled to report results
for the first quarter ended June 30 today. Profit may more than
double from a year earlier, according to Namrata Sharma, an
analyst at Dolat Capital Market Pvt. in Mumbai.  
 Investors are buying the shares on expectations of higher
 earnings , Sharma, who has an “accumulate” rating on the stock,
said by telephone. “We expect the company’s net sales to grow
at 25 percent for the next two years,” she said.  
 Net income may reach 140 million rupees ($3 million),
Sharma said. Profit rose 31 percent to 50.2 million rupees in
the quarter ended June 30, 2009, according to figures on the
company’s  website .  
